---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import AccordionItem from '../components/AccordionItem.astro';
---

<Layout title="FAQ -- mailypoppins" description="Frequently asked questions and troubleshooting for mailypoppins.">
  <Nav />
  <main id="main-content" class="content page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Common questions and troubleshooting.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 id="general">General</h2>
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <AccordionItem question="Config file not found">
          <p>
            Run <code>email config init</code> to create the config file at
            <code>~/.config/email/config.toml</code>. The interactive wizard will walk you through
            SMTP/IMAP credentials, test connections, discover server mailboxes, and assign roles.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Password not found in keyring">
          <p>
            Run <code>email config set-password</code> to store your SMTP or IMAP password in the
            OS keyring (macOS Keychain, Windows Credential Manager, or Linux Secret Service).
            Passwords are never stored in the config file.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Email not approved for sending">
          <p>
            The draft workflow requires explicit approval before sending. Run
            <code>email mark-approved &lt;file&gt;</code> or press <code>A</code> in the TUI to
            change a draft's status from <code>draft</code> to <code>approved</code>. Only approved
            emails can be sent. To reverse an accidental approval, press <code>D</code> in the TUI
            (or run <code>email mark-draft &lt;file&gt;</code>) and the draft is editable again.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="SMTP authentication failed">
          <p>
            Check your credentials with <code>email config show</code> and re-run
            <code>email config set-password smtp</code> if needed. For OAuth2 accounts, try
            <code>email config oauth2-login</code> to refresh the token.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Signature file not found">
          <p>
            Check the path in your config under <code>[signatures]</code>. Paths support
            <code>~</code> expansion. Verify the file exists at the specified location with
            <code>ls</code> or <code>email config show</code>.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="oauth2-exchange">OAuth2 / Exchange</h2>
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <AccordionItem question="IMAP is disabled for my organization">
          <p>
            Your Microsoft 365 tenant may have IMAP disabled. Contact IT to enable it, or use
            <code>auth_method = "graph"</code> in your account config, which bypasses IMAP/SMTP
            entirely and uses the Microsoft Graph API for all mail operations.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Needs admin consent for API permissions">
          <p>
            The <code>IMAP.AccessAsUser.All</code> and <code>SMTP.Send</code> permissions often
            require admin consent. Request your IT administrator to grant consent via Azure portal
            &gt; Entra ID &gt; App registrations &gt; API permissions.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="OAuth2 token expired">
          <p>
            Run <code>email config oauth2-login --account &lt;name&gt;</code> to re-authenticate.
            Access tokens expire after roughly one hour and are auto-refreshed, but refresh tokens
            expire after approximately 90 days of inactivity.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="AUTHENTICATE failed with OAuth2">
          <p>
            This can mean IMAP is disabled for the account, the token has wrong scopes, or admin
            consent is missing. Check the app permissions in Azure and ensure IMAP is enabled. If
            your tenant blocks IMAP, consider switching to <code>auth_method = "graph"</code>.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="sync-workflow">Sync and Workflow</h2>
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <AccordionItem question="How does sync work?">
          <p>
            <code>email sync</code> is additive by default -- it only downloads new emails,
            deduplicating by Message-ID. It uses a two-pass approach: first fetches headers (~50
            bytes per message) to check what is new, then downloads full messages only for emails
            not already stored locally. Add <code>--reconcile</code> to also detect server-side
            moves and deletes.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="What does reconciliation do?">
          <p>
            With <code>--reconcile</code>, sync compares local files against server state for INBOX
            and Archive. Emails moved on the server are moved locally to match. Emails deleted on
            the server are removed locally. The Sent directory is never reconciled -- locally-authored
            files are the source of truth.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Can I use mailypoppins with multiple accounts?">
          <p>
            Yes. Use the <code>[[accounts]]</code> array in <code>config.toml</code>. Each account
            has its own SMTP/IMAP settings, directories, and mailboxes. Switch between accounts in
            the TUI with the backtick key (<code>`</code>) or <code>Ctrl+1-9</code>.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="How are attachments handled?">
          <p>
            Incoming attachments are saved in a <code>_attachments/</code> subdirectory next to the
            email's <code>.md</code> file. Frontmatter records filenames. Use <code>o</code> in the
            TUI to open an attachment, or <code>O</code> to save it to a chosen directory. For
            outgoing drafts, list file paths in the <code>attachments:</code> frontmatter field.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Does it support HTML emails?">
          <p>
            Outgoing emails are written in Markdown and converted to HTML for sending, with a
            plaintext fallback. Incoming emails are stored as plaintext (<code>.md</code>) with the
            original HTML saved as a companion <code>.html</code> file. Press <code>b</code> in the
            TUI to open the HTML version in your browser.
          </p>
        </AccordionItem>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding-top: var(--space-16);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-subtext0);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .accordion-group {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
